<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="554" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,769,1190]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,769,794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of this genus are easily recognized by having following features: tarsal hind claws in both sexes single and long; third segment of palpus swollen, with small rounded sensory pit; wing with or without dark pattern; hind femur and tibia swollen, unarmed, with distinct spines; two seminal capsules; aedeagus with proximal and distal pieces. This worldwide distributed genus now includes 59 species. From the Middle East two species are recorded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="554" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,769,1190]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,949,974]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Discussion.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Clastrier &amp; Delecolle, 1990" authorityName="Clastrier &amp; Delecolle" authorityYear="1990" box="[484,957,949,974]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Boreohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,612,949,974]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Boreohelea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Clastrier" box="[626,957,949,974]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" refString="Clastrier, J. &amp; Delecolle, J. C. (1990) Description d'un nouveau genre et de nouvelles especes africaines des genres Allohelea Kieffer, Monohelea Kieffer, Downeshelea Wirth &amp; Grogan, Boreohelea nov. gen. (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 26, 129 - 157." type="journal article" year="1990">Clastrier &amp; Delécolle, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed for 
<taxonomicName authority="Clastrier &amp; Delecolle, 1990" authorityName="Clastrier &amp; Delecolle" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Boreohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afrotropica">
<emphasis box="[1168,1435,949,974]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Boreohelea afrotropica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Clastrier" box="[151,462,985,1010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" refString="Clastrier, J. &amp; Delecolle, J. C. (1990) Description d'un nouveau genre et de nouvelles especes africaines des genres Allohelea Kieffer, Monohelea Kieffer, Downeshelea Wirth &amp; Grogan, Boreohelea nov. gen. (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 26, 129 - 157." type="journal article" year="1990">Clastrier &amp; Delécolle, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described from a female with pale wings and subcylindrical fourth tarsomeres on fore and mid legs (
<bibRefCitation author="Clastrier" box="[315,630,1021,1046]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" refString="Clastrier, J. &amp; Delecolle, J. C. (1990) Description d'un nouveau genre et de nouvelles especes africaines des genres Allohelea Kieffer, Monohelea Kieffer, Downeshelea Wirth &amp; Grogan, Boreohelea nov. gen. (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 26, 129 - 157." type="journal article" year="1990">Clastrier &amp; Delécolle 1990</bibRefCitation>
). All other characters as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1917" box="[949,1056,1021,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Allohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[949,1056,1021,1046]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Allohelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently described male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Szadziewski et al. 2011" authorityName="Szadziewski et al." authorityYear="2011" box="[151,655,1057,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Allohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vespertilio">
<emphasis box="[151,383,1057,1082]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Allohelea vespertilio</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Szadziewski" box="[390,655,1057,1082]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" refString="Szadziewski, R., Gwizdalska-Kentzer, M. &amp; Gilka, W. (2011) Order Diptera, family Ceratopogonidae. In: Sheikh Tahnoon Bin Zayed Al Nahyan, H. H. (Patron) &amp; van Harten, A. (Ed.), Arthropod fauna of the United Arab Emirates. Volume 4. Dar Al Ummah Printing, Publishing, Distribution &amp; Advertising, Abu Dhabi, UAE, pp. 636 - 653." type="book" year="2011">
Szadziewski 
<emphasis box="[537,594,1057,1082]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with pale wings has also subcylindrical fourth tarsomeres of fore and mid legs like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clastrier &amp; Delecolle" authorityYear="1990" box="[316,580,1093,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Boreohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afrotropica">
<emphasis box="[316,580,1093,1118]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Boreohelea afrotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however it has genitalia with unique aedeagus composed of two pieces typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1917" box="[273,381,1129,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Allohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,381,1129,1154]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Allohelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wirth" box="[394,645,1129,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" refString="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Grogan, W. L. (1988) The predaceous midges of the World. (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae; Tribe Ceratopogonini). Flora and Fauna Handbook 4. E. J. Brill. New York, 160 pp." type="book" year="1988">Wirth &amp; Grogan 1988</bibRefCitation>
, de 
<bibRefCitation author="Meillon" box="[689,944,1129,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" refString="de Meillon, B. &amp; Wirth, W. W. (1991) The genera and subgenera (excluding Culicoides) of the Afrotropical Biting Midges (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Annals of the Natal Museum, 32, 27 - 147." type="journal article" year="1991">Meillon &amp; Wirth 1991</bibRefCitation>
). This suggests that the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clastrier &amp; Delecolle" authorityYear="1990" box="[1283,1411,1129,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Boreohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1411,1129,1154]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Boreohelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not necessary, when we expand limits of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1917" box="[724,831,1165,1190]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Allohelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[724,831,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Allohelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including there species without patterned wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
